After some investigation i found that a part of the problem is probably located in {{SakaiRubricStudentButton.js}} 

{noformat}releaseEvaluation() {

  let url = `/api/sites/${this.siteId}/rubric-evaluations/tools/${this.toolId}/items/${this.entityId}/evaluations/${this.evaluatedItemId}`;
  return fetch(url, { credentials: "include" })
  .then(r => {

    if (r.status === 200) {
      return r.json();
    }

    if (r.status !== 204) {
      throw new Error(`Network error while getting evaluation at ${url}`);
    }

    return null;
  })
  .then(async data => {
    const evaluation = data._embedded.evaluations[0];
    if (evaluation) {
      evaluation.status = 2;
      url = `/api/sites/${this.siteId}/rubric-evaluations/${evaluation.id}`;
      await fetch(url, {
        body: JSON.stringify(evaluation),
        credentials: "include",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        method: "PATCH",
      })
      .then(r => {
        if (!r.ok) {
          throw new Error("Failed to release evaluation");
        }
      });
    }
  }){noformat}

The response object is expected to have the {{_embedded}} property containing the evaluation. But the api seems to produce plain json object containing the evaluation.

!image-20240606-083100.png|width=100%,alt="image-20240606-083100.png"!

!json_eval-20240606-080819.png|width=75%,alt="json_eval-20240606-080819.png"!



Another part of the problem is probably that the Patch call contains plain json object containing the evaluation:

{{ headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },}}

But the corresponding API endpoint does require {{application/json-patch+json}}.

