08/Mar/24 7:13 PM;557058:1fab5062-c88f-4d13-b5c9-a1e08a1b6779;What I think is happening is that in PublishedAssessentSettings.java

{noformat}// deal with releaseTo
this.releaseTo = accessControl.getReleaseTo(); // list of String
this.publishingTargets = getPublishingTargets();
this.targetSelected = getTargetSelected(releaseTo);
this.firstTargetSelected = getFirstTargetSelected(releaseTo);{noformat}

firstTargetSelected gets set to the releaseTo value of SAM_PUBLISHEDACCESSCONTROL_T.releaseto, which is the “old” site title

then in the same java file’s *getPublishingTargets()* method, it sets up the Availability dropdown to use the new site title

so then in *publishedSettings.jsp*

{noformat}<h:selectOneMenu id="releaseTo" disabled="true" value="#{publishedSettings.firstTargetSelected}" onclick="setBlockDivs();">{noformat}

it tries to set the selected option to the firstTargetSelected, which is the “old” title, but since no options exist with that value, it defaults to the 1st and wrong option.

perhaps instead of setting SAM_PUBLISHEDACCESSCONTROL_T.releaseto to the site title, it should be set to “Entire Site” (or “entire_site”) or the site_id.  And the Availability dropdown value for “should match either “Entire Site” or the site_id.  Or is there another reason the releaseTo is set to the title?  But also , this would affect many records in SAM_PUBLISHEDACCESSCONTROL_T, so you’d have to account for “Entire Site” or “title”…. or write a databaese conversion script to change all of the “titles” to “Entire Site” (where releaseTo != “Anonymous User” and releaseTo != “Selected Groups” and releaseTo != '')

