                }
            } catch (PermissionException e) {
                log.warn("User doesn't have permission to access submission, {}", e.getMessage());
            }
        }
        return false;
    }{noformat}

in the first if block the opentime condition is false so it falls through the else and returns false, thus throwing the exception.  I’m not sure why 23+ doesn’t fail, the code looks the same… the calling function throws the exception, but maybe something further down the chain catches it in 23+?

